h1. jQuery

Provides an AMD wrapper around jQuery with the "jquery" module name. 
While jQuery 1.7 onwards supports AMD if the define.amd.jquery property is true, we do not have a loader in play at the time jQuery is executed. We therefore define the "jquery" module at a point where we have a loader.

The version of this wrapper is consistent with the jQuery version it wraps.

h2. Usage

Include the following dependency in your POM to make jQuery available to your project:

{code}
<project>
    <dependencies>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.codehaus.mojo</groupId>
            <artifactId>jquery</artifactId>
            <version>${projectVersion}</version>
            <type>js</type>
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>
</project>
{code}